main event: Reports of unidentified flying objects near Dublin, Ohio, on multiple occasions in 1952 and 1959.
interesting points: The first sighting was recorded by ground radar with a duration of 31 minutes,The description included sightings of circular, greenish-white objects observed at various times,An observer noted sighting five steady, bright, orange-white objects in formation during a clear night,The radar sighting lacked any visible contact, common in radar-only reports,The observation lasted for several minutes and included movements such as hovering and disappearing.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects (one radar detected, five visually observed)
witness description: An individual observer with visual contact of the objects.
